radiographic_examinations.findings: Normal spontaneous phasic flow and compressibility within the right internal jugular, axillary, brachial and cephalic veins. A PICC line is visualized within the right basilic vein, demonstrating normal spontaneous flow. Spontaneous phasic flow is present in the right subclavian vein. A vessel is identified in the area of previous IV placement in the right wrist with no flow identified and subcutaneous edema in this region.
